## 1.4 — Real-time Architecture

```
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
WebSocket Architecture
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Problem: Multiple instances of Messaging Service
         يجب أن يصل الـ message لأي instance

Solution: Redis Pub/Sub as Message Broker

Flow:
Client A → WS → Instance 1
Client B → WS → Instance 2

Message A→B:
  1. Instance 1 receives message
  2. Saves to PostgreSQL
  3. Publishes to Redis channel: "user:{B_id}"
  4. Instance 2 subscribes to "user:{B_id}"
  5. Instance 2 delivers to Client B via WS

Rooms (Deal Day, Group):
  Redis channel: "room:{room_id}"
  All instances subscribe to active rooms

Connection Management:
  On Connect:   SET user:{id}:socket → instance_id (Redis)
  On Disconnect: DEL user:{id}:socket
  Heartbeat:    Ping every 30s

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Event-Driven Architecture
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Event Bus: Redis Pub/Sub (Phase 1)
           → Migrate to Kafka (Phase 3+)

Event Schema:
{
  "event_id": "uuid",
  "event_type": "deal_room.visited",
  "version": "1.0",
  "timestamp": "ISO8601",
  "source_service": "deal-service",
  "actor_id": "user_uuid",
  "payload": {
    // event-specific data
  },
  "metadata": {
    "correlation_id": "uuid",
    "environment": "production"
  }
}

Critical Event Flows:

1. DEAL ROOM VISITED:
   Deal Service → PUBLISHES → deal_room.visited
   ↓
   Notification Service → SUBSCRIBES → notifies Founder
   Analytics Service → SUBSCRIBES → logs event
   AI Service → SUBSCRIBES → updates interest signals

2. STARTUP GRADUATED:
   Accelerator Service → PUBLISHES → startup.graduated
   ↓
   Deal Service → creates Verified Pipeline entry
   Marketplace Service → adds to listings
   Notification Service → notifies startup founder

3. DEAL CLOSED:
   Deal Service → PUBLISHES → deal.closed
   ↓
   Cap Table Service → creates entry
   Analytics Service → updates metrics
   Feed Service → creates announcement post
   Notification Service → congratulations
   AI Service → trains matching model
```

