## 2.2 — Architecture Decision Records (ADRs)

```
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
ADR-001: Microservices vs Monolith
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Decision: Modular Monolith → Microservices

Rationale:
Phase 1: Modular Monolith
  → أسرع في البناء
  → أقل complexity
  → فريق صغير يديره بسهولة
  → يمكن تقسيمه لاحقاً

Phase 3+: Full Microservices
  → Scale مستقل لكل service
  → تقنيات مختلفة حسب الحاجة
  → fault isolation

Migration Path:
  Monolith بـ Domain Modules →
  Extract services تدريجياً →
  Full Microservices

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
ADR-002: Flutter vs React Native vs Native
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Decision: Flutter

Why not React Native:
  → Bridge overhead
  → JSI improvement but still not native
  → Fragmented ecosystem

Why not Native (Swift + Kotlin):
  → 2x development cost
  → 2x team size
  → مشكلة RTL تحتاج حل مزدوج

Why Flutter:
  ✅ Single codebase iOS + Android + Web
  ✅ Skia rendering = consistent UI
  ✅ RTL support built-in وممتاز
  ✅ Performance ممتازة للـ Social apps
  ✅ Arabic font rendering ممتاز

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
ADR-003: PostgreSQL vs MongoDB
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Decision: PostgreSQL

Why PostgreSQL wins:
  ✅ ACID transactions (للـ Cap Table والـ Deals)
  ✅ Complex joins للعلاقات
  ✅ JSONB للـ flexible fields
  ✅ Row-level security (RLS)
  ✅ pgvector للـ embeddings
  ✅ Mature ecosystem
  ✅ Better for financial data

When to use MongoDB:
  → لو كانت البيانات document-heavy فقط
  → لو لا توجد علاقات معقدة

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
ADR-004: REST vs GraphQL
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Decision: REST (Primary) + GraphQL (Feed only)

REST for:
  → CRUD operations
  → Simple request/response
  → Caching (easier with REST)
  → Developer familiarity

GraphQL for:
  → Feed (complex nested queries)
  → Real-time subscriptions
  → Mobile (reduces over-fetching)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
ADR-005: Redis Pub/Sub vs Kafka
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Phase 1 Decision: Redis Pub/Sub

Rationale:
  → Redis موجود بالفعل للـ Cache
  → No additional infra
  → Simpler operations
  → Sufficient for < 10K events/second

Phase 3 Migration to Kafka when:
  → Events > 10K/second
  → Need event replay
  → Need event sourcing
  → Multiple consumer groups needed
```

