## 5.1 — Security Architecture

```
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
LAYER 1: NETWORK SECURITY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

DDoS Protection:
  Provider: AWS Shield Advanced
  Threshold: Auto-mitigation
  Alerting: PagerDuty P1

WAF Rules (AWS WAF):
  → Block SQL Injection patterns
  → Block XSS patterns
  → Block known bad IPs (AbuseIPDB)
  → Rate limit by IP: 100 req/min
  → Geo-blocking: configurable
  → Bot detection: CAPTCHA for suspicious

Network Isolation:
  → All services in Private subnets
  → Internet access via NAT Gateway only
  → Services communicate via VPC internally
  → No direct internet access to databases

TLS:
  → TLS 1.3 minimum
  → TLS 1.0/1.1 disabled
  → Certificate: AWS ACM (auto-renew)
  → HSTS header enforced

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
LAYER 2: AUTHENTICATION SECURITY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

JWT Strategy:
  Algorithm:          RS256 (asymmetric)
  Access Token TTL:   15 minutes
  Refresh Token TTL:  30 days
  Key Rotation:       Monthly (automated)

  Payload:
  {
    "sub": "user_id",
    "role": "FOUNDER",
    "ver_level": 2,
    "plan": "PRO",
    "iat": 1234567890,
    "exp": 1234568790,
    "jti": "unique_token_id"  ← للـ revocation
  }

Token Security:
  → Refresh Token: stored as httpOnly cookie
  → Access Token: in-memory (not localStorage)
  → Token Rotation: new refresh on every use
  → Blacklist: Redis SET with TTL

Password Security:
  → bcrypt with cost factor 12
  → Minimum 8 chars
  → Common passwords list check (10K list)
  → Breached password check (HaveIBeenPwned API)
  → No password hints stored

Brute Force Protection:
  → 5 failed attempts → 15 min lockout
  → 10 failed attempts → 24h lockout
  → Email notification on lockout
  → Admin can unlock manually

MFA:
  → TOTP (Google Authenticator compatible)
  → SMS backup
  → Backup codes (10 codes, single use)
  → Required for: Accelerator Admins, VCs

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
LAYER 3: AUTHORIZATION (RBAC)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Roles Hierarchy:
  ADMIN > ACCELERATOR_ADMIN > FOUNDER >
  INVESTOR > OPERATOR > ANGEL > USER

Permission Matrix:
┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Resource         │ Owner │ Member │ Public│
├──────────────────┼───────┼────────┼───────┤
│ Company Profile  │ CRUD  │  R     │  R*   │
│ Deal Room        │ CRUD  │  R     │  R*   │
│ Cohort Data      │ CRUD  │  R     │  ─    │
│ Scorecard        │ CRUD  │  ─     │  ─    │
│ Cap Table        │ CRUD  │  R     │  ─    │
│ Messages         │ CRUD  │  CRUD  │  ─    │
│ Posts            │ CRUD  │  CR    │  R    │
└──────────────────┴───────┴────────┴───────┘
*R = Read (based on privacy settings)

Row-Level Security (PostgreSQL RLS):
  ALTER TABLE deal_room_documents
  ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

  CREATE POLICY "owner_access" ON deal_room_documents
    FOR ALL
    USING (
      EXISTS (
        SELECT 1 FROM deal_rooms dr
        WHERE dr.id = deal_room_id
        AND dr.owner_id = current_setting('app.user_id')::UUID
      )
    );

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
LAYER 4: DATA SECURITY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Encryption at Rest:
  Database:     AWS RDS encryption (AES-256)
  S3:           SSE-S3 (AES-256)
  Redis:        ElastiCache encryption
  Backups:      Encrypted by default

Field-level Encryption (sensitive fields):
  → phone numbers
  → national ID (if collected)
  → bank account info (future)
  Library: AWS Encryption SDK

Data Masking:
  → Logs: mask phone/email
  → Analytics: anonymize PII
  → Error reports: no PII in Sentry

Secrets Management:
  → AWS Secrets Manager for:
     DB credentials, API keys
  → HashiCorp Vault for:
     Dynamic secrets, PKI
  → No secrets in code or ENV files
  → Secret rotation: automated monthly

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
LAYER 5: APPLICATION SECURITY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Input Validation (Zod schemas):
  → All API inputs validated
  → Types enforced at compile time (TypeScript)
  → SQL injection: impossible (Prisma ORM)
  → XSS: DOMPurify on frontend
        + sanitize-html on backend

File Upload Security:
  → Whitelist MIME types only
  → Validate file header (magic bytes)
  → Max file size enforced
  → Virus scan: ClamAV on upload
  → Files renamed (UUID) on S3
  → No direct S3 URLs (presigned only)

Rate Limiting (per endpoint):
  Auth endpoints:    5 req/minute
  OTP endpoints:     3 req/minute
  API general:       100 req/minute
  AI endpoints:      10 req/minute
  File upload:       5 req/minute

CORS Policy:
  Allowed Origins:
    https://majlis.io
    https://app.majlis.io
    https://admin.majlis.io
  Credentials: true
  Methods: GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE, OPTIONS

Security Headers:
  Content-Security-Policy: strict
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(self)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
LAYER 6: AUDIT & MONITORING
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Audit Log (immutable):
  Events logged:
  → Authentication (login/logout/failed)
  → Authorization failures
  → Data access (sensitive resources)
  → Data modification (Cap Table, Deals)
  → Admin actions
  → File access (Data Room)

  Schema:
  {
    timestamp, user_id, action,
    resource_type, resource_id,
    ip_address, user_agent,
    old_value, new_value,
    success, reason
  }

  Storage: Write-only table in separate DB
  Retention: 7 years (legal requirement)

Security Monitoring:
  → CloudTrail: AWS API calls
  → GuardDuty: Threat detection
  → Security Hub: Centralized findings
  → Custom alerts: Suspicious patterns

Penetration Testing:
  → Annual third-party pentest
  → Bug bounty program (Phase 2)
  → Automated SAST: SonarQube
  → Automated DAST: OWASP ZAP
```

